learning_notes.sentence: *Hola,* ¿cómo estás? Yo estoy muy bien hoy.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: Hello, how are you? I am very well today.

learning_notes.sentence: Ella dijo *adiós* a su amigo.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: She said goodbye to her friend.

learning_notes.sentence: Muchas *gracias* por tu ayuda con la tarea de español.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: Thank you very much for your help with the Spanish homework.

learning_notes.sentence: ¿Me puedes traer un vaso de agua, *por* favor?
learning_notes.sentence_translation: Can you bring me a glass of water, please?

learning_notes.sentence: *Sí,* por favor, tráeme un vaso de agua fría.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: Yes, please, bring me a glass of cold water.

learning_notes.sentence: *No,* ego non ibo ad festa in nocte.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: No, I will not go to the party tonight.

learning_notes.sentence: Yo quiero beber un poco de *agua.*
learning_notes.sentence_translation: I want to drink a little water.

learning_notes.sentence: Necesito preparar la *comida* para mi familia hoy.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: I need to prepare the food for my family today.

learning_notes.sentence: La *casa* es grande y tiene un jardín bonito.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The house is big and has a pretty garden.

learning_notes.sentence: El *perro* juega con la pelota en el jardín.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The dog plays with the ball in the garden.

learning_notes.sentence: El *gato* es muy bonito y juega en el jardín.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The cat is very pretty and plays in the garden.

learning_notes.sentence: Mi amigo compró un *libro* nuevo en la librería hoy.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: My friend bought a new book at the bookstore today.

learning_notes.sentence: La niña pone su vaso de agua en la *mesa.*
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The girl puts her glass of water on the table.

learning_notes.sentence: La *silla* está al lado de la mesa.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The chair is next to the table.

learning_notes.sentence: El perro está al lado de la *puerta.*
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The dog is next to the door.

learning_notes.sentence: Quiero abrir la *ventana* porque hace mucho calor.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: I want to open the window because it's very hot.

learning_notes.sentence: Ella tiene mucho que hacer durante el *día.*
learning_notes.sentence_translation: She has a lot to do during the day.

learning_notes.sentence: Me gusta mirar las estrellas por la *noche.*
learning_notes.sentence_translation: I like to look at the stars at night.

learning_notes.sentence: El *sol* brilla mucho hoy.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The sun shines a lot today.

learning_notes.sentence: Me gusta ver la *luna* por la noche.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: I like to see the moon at night.

learning_notes.sentence: Mi *amigo* y yo vamos a jugar fútbol esta tarde.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: My friend and I are going to play soccer this afternoon.

learning_notes.sentence: Ella vive con su *familia* en una casa bonita.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: She lives with her family in a nice house.

learning_notes.sentence: Mi *madre* lee un libro interesante en el sofá.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: My mother reads an interesting book on the sofa.

learning_notes.sentence: Mi *padre* es alto.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: My father is tall.

learning_notes.sentence: Mi *hermano* mayor siempre juega conmigo en el parque.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: My older brother always plays with me in the park.

learning_notes.sentence: Ella es mi *hermana* y tiene el pelo rubio.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: She is my sister and has blonde hair.

learning_notes.sentence: La maestra enseña en la *escuela* a los estudiantes.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The teacher teaches the students at school.

learning_notes.sentence: Ella siempre llega temprano a su *trabajo* por la mañana.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: She always arrives early to her work in the morning.

learning_notes.sentence: Los niños juegan en la *calle* todos los días.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The children play in the street every day.

learning_notes.sentence: Vivimos en una *ciudad* muy grande y ocupada.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: We live in a very big and busy city.

learning_notes.sentence: España es un *país* bonito.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: Spain is a beautiful country.

learning_notes.sentence: Me gusta viajar por el *mundo* y conocer lugares nuevos.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: I like to travel the world and get to know new places.

learning_notes.sentence: El *tiempo* está muy bueno para salir hoy.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The weather is very good to go out today.

learning_notes.sentence: Vamos a visitar a mi familia el próximo *año.*
learning_notes.sentence_translation: We are going to visit my family next year.

learning_notes.sentence: Este *mes* vamos a la playa con mi familia.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: This **month** we are going to the beach with my family.

learning_notes.sentence: La *semana* tiene siete días en total.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The week has seven days in total.

learning_notes.sentence: Necesito una *hora* más para terminar mi tarea.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: I need one more hour to finish my homework.

learning_notes.sentence: Por favor, espera un *minuto* aquí conmigo.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: Please, wait a minute here with me.

learning_notes.sentence: Por favor, escribe tu *nombre* en el papel.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: Please, write your name on the paper.

learning_notes.sentence: Ella preguntó mi *edad* porque me veo joven.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: She asked my age because I look young.

learning_notes.sentence: El *niño* juega en el parque.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The child plays in the park.

learning_notes.sentence: Un *hombre* lee un libro en el parque.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: A man reads a book in the park.

learning_notes.sentence: La *mujer* lee un libro interesante en el parque.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The woman reads an interesting book in the park.

learning_notes.sentence: El *chico* pequeño juega con la pelota en el parque.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The small boy plays with the ball in the park.

learning_notes.sentence: La *chica* joven camina lentamente por el sendero verde.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The young girl walks slowly along the green path.

learning_notes.sentence: El parque cerca de mi casa es muy *grande.*
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The park near my house is very big.

learning_notes.sentence: Ella tiene un pájaro muy *pequeño* en su jaula.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: She has a very small bird in her cage.

learning_notes.sentence: Hoy es un día muy *bueno* para salir.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: Today is a very good day to go out.

learning_notes.sentence: El café de esta tienda es bastante *malo* hoy.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: The coffee from this shop is quite bad today.

learning_notes.sentence: Mi hermana está *feliz* porque visitó a sus amigos.
learning_notes.sentence_translation: My sister is happy because she visited her friends.
